What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
int main() {
    for (int i{1}; i <= 6; ++i) {
        if (i == 4) break;
        if (i % 2 == 0) continue;
        std::cout << i << " ";
    }
    std::cout << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```

This program is supposed to print all odd numbers from 1 to 9, one per line. What is the bug?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
int main() {
    int i{1};
    while (i <= 9) {
        if (i % 2 == 0) {
            continue;
        }
        std::cout << i << "\n";
        ++i;
    }
    return 0;
}
```

What does this program print?

